Problem:
class WeatherSimulator {
    int temperature = 20;
    boolean isRaining = false;

    void setTemperature(int newTemp) {
        temperature = newTemp;
        if (temperature < 5) {
            isRaining = true;
        }
    }

    void makeItRain() {
        isRaining = true;
        if (isRaining) {
            temperature -= 5;
        }
    }
}",

If it is observed to be raining, can we infer the temperature dropped below 5 without any intervention?
